{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"content":["Cut 6 pancetta slices into pieces, then transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Line 2 baking trays with 2 large rectangular pieces of aluminium foil (approx. 30 cm x 40 cm). Placing longer edge of aluminium foil in front of you, lay 10 pancetta slices, vertically down piece of foil, overlapping each slice of pancetta slightly with the next. Repeat with other piece of aluminium foil and remaining 10 pancetta slices. Set pancetta-lined foil pieces aside.","Place bread in mixing bowl and grate <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place sage, onions, garlic, parsley, butter and reserved pancetta pieces in mixing bowl then chop <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then chop again <nobr>3 sec\/speed 7<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula, then sauté <nobr>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 1<\/nobr>. Set mixing bowl aside and allow to cool slightly (approx. 10-15 minutes).","Add all remaining ingredients and reserved breadcrumbs then combine <nobr>10 sec\/\/speed 4<\/nobr>. Transfer to a ceramic or glass bowl to cool completely (15 minutes). Meanwhile, preheat oven to 180°C.","Once stuffing mixture has cooled, place half of stuffing mixture horizontally down middle of pancetta on 1 aluminium sheet. Wrap pancetta ends over stuffing to enclose, then wrap aluminium foil around pancetta to form a sausage shape. Repeat with remaining stuffing and second sheet of pancetta-lined aluminium foil.","Return wrapped sausages to baking trays then bake for 40 minutes (180°C), or until pancetta is crispy and coloured. Serve warm."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"","content":["26 slices pancetta (approx. 350 g), thick cut and rind removed","250 g white bread, slightly stale, torn into pieces (3 cm)","3 fresh sage leaves","2 onions, halved","2 garlic cloves","8 sprig fresh flat-leaf parsley (approx. 15 g), leaves only","80 g butter, diced","12 dried apricots (approx. 70 g), cut in pieces","50 g dried cranberries","¼ tsp fine sea salt, or to taste","¼ tsp ground black pepper, or to taste","½ tsp ground allspice","1 Tbsp apricot jam","2 large eggs"]}],"id":"r131716","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-2JSMy1bnY98\/XZWYS6GbvTI\/AAAAAAAAd7w\/nzMItvK8YggJ625WvYMAESa4RbN06UisgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_6T36CH1N7DtTQ-U8.png","title":"Pancetta-Wrapped Apricot Stuffing Roll (Australia)","publishedAt":"2016-12-05T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"14 g","fat":"14 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"19 g","calories":"1110 kJ \/ 264 kcal"},"usefulItems":"2 baking trays (approx. 40 cm x 35 cm), aluminium foil, bowl, oven","hintsAndTricks":["This recipe can be made in advance and frozen. Place the stuffing roll into the freezer after rolling and wrapping in aluminium foil in step 6. Allow to thaw before proceeding as per recipe to bake in step 7.","<strong>Bacon-Wrapped Apricot Stuffing Roll<\/strong>: Substitute the pancetta slices with 13 bacon rashers. Cut 3 of the bacon rashers into pieces and set aside in step 1. Use 5 bacon rashers to line each sheet of aluminium foil in step 2 and proceed as per recipe."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","10 portions"]}